SIMPLE: tuberous
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Tuberous
<hw>Tu"ber*ous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>tuberosus</ets>: cf. F. <ets>tub⟦eacute⟧reux</ets>. See
<er>Tuber</er>, and cf. also <er>Tuberose</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Covered with knobby or wartlike prominences;
knobbed.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Consisting of, or bearing, tubers;
resembling a tuber.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Tu"ber*ous*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tube-shell</ent>⟦br⟧
